> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/ZPowers/Basic.html#Subgroup.zpowers\">Subgroup.zpowers</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Preadditive/Projective/Resolution.html#CategoryTheory.ProjectiveResolution\">CategoryTheory.ProjectiveResolution</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Rep.html#Rep.trivial\">trivial</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a finite cyclic group `G` generated by `g : G`, this is the projective resolution of `k`\nas a trivial `k`-linear `G`-representation given by periodic complex\n`... ⟶ k[G] --N--> k[G] --(ρ(g) - 𝟙)--> k[G] --N--> k[G] --(ρ(g) - 𝟙)--> k[G] ⟶ 0` where `ρ` is\nthe left regular representation and `N` is the norm map. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.resolution","kind":"def","line":216,"name":"Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.resolution","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.lean#L216-L226"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.resolution_quasiIso\"><span class=\"name\">Rep</span>.<span class=\"name\">FiniteCyclicGroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">resolution_quasiIso</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\