f=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.chainComplexFunctor\">chainComplexFunctor</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/HomologicalComplex.html#HomologicalComplex.Hom.f\">f</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.chainComplexFunctor_map_f","kind":"theorem","line":128,"name":"Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.chainComplexFunctor_map_f","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.lean#L128-L128"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.chainComplexFunctor\"><span class=\"name\">Rep</span>.<span class=\"name\">FiniteCyclicGroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">chainComplexFunctor</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#CommGroup\">CommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Defs.html#Fintype\">Fintype</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">CategoryTheory.Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Rep.html#Rep\">Rep</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/HomologicalComplex.html#ChainComplex\">ChainComplex</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Rep.html#Rep\">Rep</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a finite group `G` and `g : G`, this is the functor `Rep k G ⥤ ChainComplex (Rep k G) ℕ`\nsending `A : Rep k G` to the periodic chain complex in `Rep k G` given by\n`... ⟶ A --N--> A --(ρ(g) - 𝟙)--> A --N--> A --(ρ(g) - 𝟙)--> A ⟶ 0`\nwhere `N` is the norm map. When `G` is generated by `g` and `A` is the left regular representation\n`k[G]`, it is a projective resolution of `k` as a trivial representation.\n\nIt sends a morphism `f : A ⟶ B` to the chain morphism defined by `f` in every degree. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/FiniteCyclic.html#Rep.FiniteCyclicGroup.chainComplexFunctor","kind":"def","line":121,"name":"Rep.FiniteCyclicGro